{
  "texts": [
    "It was found that simpler models, while more interpretable, often suffer from reduced accuracy in complex tasks, suggesting a trade-off that must be navigated [24,25,26].",
    "The development of explainability frameworks has similarly focused on bridging the gap between human cognitive capabilities and the inherent complexity of machine learning algorithms [27,28,29,30,31].",
    "Research has found the importance of these frameworks in facilitating trust and transparency, especially in applications with significant social or personal implications [32,33].",
    "Furthermore, there is a need for standardization in the measurement and evaluation of interpretability and explainability, highlighting the diversity of approaches in quantifying these concepts [34,27,35].",
    "This part of related work establishes a foundation upon which practical applications and methodologies can be built, emphasizing the importance of aligning technical advancements with human understanding and ethical standards."
  ]
}